[l] Verschwoerungstheorie des Tages:Bank of America’s online banking app requires you to accept microphones and cameras. McAfee called Bank of America and asked why they require microphones and cameras. They replied that – if you emptied all of the money in your account and said “it wasn’t me”, they could check, and then say: Well, it certainly looks like you. And it certainly sounds like you.In order to do that, B of A’s app keeps your microphone and camera on for a half hour after you’ve finished your banking
